    <entry xml:lang="en">
        <title>Genesis</title>
        <published>2026-05-18T00:00:00+00:00</published>
        <updated>2026-05-18T00:00:00+00:00</updated>
        
        <author>
          <name>
            
              Unknown
            
          </name>
        </author>
        
        <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.wheelofheaven.world/library/genesis-woh/"/>
        <id>https://www.wheelofheaven.world/library/genesis-woh/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="https://www.wheelofheaven.world/library/genesis-woh/">&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Genesis (Wheel of Heaven Translation)&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; is the first published chapter of the
&lt;a href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;github.com&#x2F;wheelofheaven&#x2F;www.wheelofheaven.io&#x2F;issues&#x2F;12&quot;&gt;Wheel of Heaven Translation Program&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;.
Genesis 1 is rendered from the pointed Hebrew Masoretic text (Westminster Leningrad
Codex, public domain) under a documented WoH lens, with the source and the English
translation displayed in parallel.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Verses with commentary carry a bracketed marker &lt;code&gt;[ ]&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; at the end of the
translated line. Click the marker to open the commentary panel.&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;
Commentaries surface the lexical decisions that distinguish this rendering
from the inherited English translations — &lt;em&gt;Elohim&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; plural, the &lt;em&gt;bara&#x2F;asah&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;
verb pattern, &lt;em&gt;raqia&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; as a hammered-out dome, the cohortative &lt;em&gt;na&#x27;aseh&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; in
v26, &lt;em&gt;tselem&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;demut&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; as physical resemblance, the polemical refusal of
&lt;em&gt;shemesh&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;yareach&lt;&#x2F;em&gt; in v14–16, and others.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a &lt;strong&gt;draft&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;. The translation is AI-drafted (Claude Opus 4.7) against
translation-glossary v1.0.0, pending human review.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
</content>
        
